Acknowledgements
Thanks to Eduardo Martins (UNBC) for being a valuable source of fisheries-related inputs and Rajtantra Lilhare
and Aseem Sharma (UNBC) for assisting with ArcMap applications. This research would not have been possible
without data providers: Dave Patterson (DFO), Jenifer Bond (Triton Environmental Consultants), Justus
Benckhuysen (Rio Tinto), and Lauren Wick and Gord Holmes (Water Survey of Canada). Thanks to Wayne
Salewski for continued support of this research. We also thank Francis Zwiers (PCIC), André St-Hilaire (INRS),
Bruno Larouche (Rio Tinto) and Phil Owens, Margot Parkes and Ellen Petticrew of the Integrated Watershed
Research Group (IWRG) at UNBC for their input on this work. Financial support for this study was provided
by the Canadian Sea Ice and Snow Evolution (CanSISE) Network (funded under the Natural Sciences and
Engineering Research Council of Canada’s (NSERC) Climate Change and Atmospheric Research (CCAR)
program) and the Nechako Environmental Enhancement Fund (NEEF). Special thanks to Marco Toffolon and
Sebastiano Piccolroaz (University of Trento, Italy) for providing access to the Air2Stream model code and user
guide. Thanks to the anonymous reviewers for constructive comments and suggestions that greatly improved this
paper.
Author Contributions
S.U.I. and S.J.D. contributed equally to design the study, R.H. performed the QA/QC on observational datasets,
S.U.I. implemented the Air2Stream model to the FRB, performed the numerical simulations and analyzed the
output data with support from R.H. R.H. and S.U.I. wrote the manuscript with contributions from S.J.D. and B.B.
and all contributed to the discussion of the results and manuscript refinement and revisions.
